subSubSection.paragraph:
Hypopygium (
Figs. 41
, 
48–49, 53–54, 56
). Tergite IX densely covered with strong macrotrichia apices of which are directed anteriorly, with 11–13 setae, 12–22 µm long (laterally setae longer) and with narrow (8–12 µm), weakly chitinized and naked anal point, 120–140 µm long (
Fig. 41
). Laterosternite IX with 9–16 setae, 24–28 µm long. Transverse sternopodeme (TSA) regular triangular, 84–108 µm high, 162–172 µm wide at the base (
Figs. 53–54
); TSA height/TSA width 0.49–0.67. Aedeagal lobe 136–168 µm long; phallapodeme sclerotized, 108–112 µm long. Gonocoxite 352–380 µm long; superior volsellae rounded–angular, along margin with 4–6 setae, 28–36 µm long (
Fig. 56
). Gonostylus 148–168 µm long, weakly curved, slightly expanded in the distal half along the outer edge (
Figs. 48–49
); in apical part with megaseta in form of wide terminal spine, 8–12 μm long and tooth the same size, next to it there is two setae approximately of the same length. HR 2.15–2.26.
